                                      "content": "Great! Now let me explain what this CI pipeline does and create a couple more useful workflows.\n\n## What Your CI Pipeline Does (Step by Step):\n\n### **Triggers** (Lines 3-9):\n- **Push to main**: Runs every time you `git push` \n- **Pull requests**: Runs when someone creates a PR\n- **Weekly schedule**: Runs Monday mornings to catch any issues\n\n### **The Job** (Lines 11-55):\n1. **Tests 4 Python versions** (3.8, 3.9, 3.10, 3.11) - ensures compatibility\n2. **Downloads your code** from GitHub\n3. **Installs dependencies** from requirements.txt\n4. **Checks code quality** with flake8 (finds bugs/style issues)\n5. **Checks formatting** with black (consistent code style)\n6. **Checks imports** with isort (organized imports)\n7. **Runs your tests** with pytest and measures coverage\n8. **Reports coverage** to see how much code is tested\n\nNow let me add a security scanning workflow:",
